    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="79"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d79">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">
                    <persName corresp="#p_LFAWD1">Leahy</persName> Papers: Telegram</note>
                <head>No. 79 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The President’s Chief of Staff</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="#p_LFAWD1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Leahy</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">President</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d79fn1">Then at Olympia, Washington.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">top secret</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">[<placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>,] <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-20">20 June
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>At the joint request of <persName corresp="#p_MGAGC1">General Marshall</persName>
                    and Mr. <persName corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> I have today sent the
                    following to <persName corresp="#p_HWA2">Harriman</persName>:<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d79fn2">As telegram No. 300.</note>
                    <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>“The President has in mind bringing his American Chiefs of Staff with him
                            to Berlin. Please ascertain <persName corresp="#p_SMIV2"
                                >Stalin</persName>’s reaction to having the Chiefs of Staff come
                            with the President, you <persName corresp="#p_HK1">Harriman</persName>
                            having in mind the possible Japanese reaction.</p>
                        <p>Early information on this question is desired.”</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Both <persName corresp="#p_MGAGC1">Marshall</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_HHL1">Hopkins</persName> doubt the advisability and see no
                    necessity of a staff meeting in Germany at this time and fear that <persName
                        corresp="#p_SMIV2">Stalin</persName> would not like it.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
